Iranian editorial writers are rejoicing

Iran's late fundamentalist patriarch, the Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini, vowed for years to unseat Saddam.
Iran frequently accuses both the U.S. and Saddam of trying to undermine the Islamic revolution.
Saddam's overthrow of the emir of Kuwait changed all that.
It noted that Kuwait had blindly supported Iraq, "little knowing that it was feeding a wild beast in her own neighborhood."
Under the Frankenstein headline, IRNA said in its own commentary: "For the time being, tiny Kuwait ... breathes no more.
According to Iran's pundits, the Great Satan planned it all.
